            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>Iriga is strategically located between Naga City in the north and Legazpi City in the south. From Manila to Naga Airport, it is a 55-minute travel and from Naga Airport to Iriga, it is a 30-minute ride by car. If you are landing at the Legazpi Airport which is an hour’s flight from Manila, Iriga is a 50-minute travel by car.</p>
            <p>Major air-conditioned bus companies ply the Manila-Bicol Route via Maharlika Highway which is an eight-hour ride. Terminals are located at the Ali-Mall Cubao, Pasay City and Pedro Gil Street, Manila. The Philippine National Railways (PNR) now travels daily the Manila – Bicol route and vice – versa.</p>
